    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Thymus vulgaris are digestive issues, including indigestion, which is alleviated by its antispasmodic properties. Thymus vulgaris also exhibits antifungal properties, making it effective against fungal infections, such as athlete's foot. Additionally, its expectorant and antimicrobial properties aid in treating respiratory infections, such as bronchitis, and respiratory problems, such as cough and sinusitis. Furthermore, Thymus vulgaris has anti-inflammatory properties, which accelerate wound healing and soothe skin irritations and insect bites, while its antiviral properties combat cold sores and gastroenteritis. Thymus vulgaris also relieves stress, alleviates diarrhea, and treats sore throat, inflammation, and common cold, in addition to promoting skin conditions, wound healing, and preventing the occurrence of respiratory infections like cough and bronchitis.",
