    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Thymus vulgaris are primarily due to its antimicrobial activity, which is attributed to the presence of volatile oils, particularly thymol, that exhibit bactericidal and fungicidal effects against a wide range of microorganisms. Additionally, the antioxidant properties of this plant are also noteworthy, as flavonoids and phenolic acids have been shown to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Its anti-inflammatory properties are also well-documented, with studies demonstrating that the bioactive compounds of Thymus vulgaris can inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Furthermore, the antiviral properties of this plant have been found to be effective against certain viral infections, with the bioactive compounds exhibiting antiviral activity against herpes simplex virus and influenza virus. The antifungal properties of Thymus vulgaris are also significant, as its bioactive compounds have been shown to inhibit the growth of various fungal species, including Candida albicans and Aspergillus niger.",
