    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effect of using Thymus vulgaris are exacerbation of allergies due to its allergenic compounds like thymol and carvacrol which can trigger severe reactions in individuals with existing allergies. Improper use of Thymus vulgaris can also lead to liver damage as its compounds can be toxic to the liver in high concentrations and prolonged use. Additionally, ingestion of Thymus vulgaris can cause nausea and vomiting due to its strong aromatic properties. Furthermore, Thymus vulgaris can interact with certain medications like blood thinners, diabetes medications, and sedatives, reducing their efficacy or increasing the risk of adverse effects. Thymus vulgaris may also trigger seizures in individuals with a history of seizure disorders due to its neurotoxic properties, especially when used in large quantities or in combination with other medications."
